ğŸ”¹ Create Event :
POST http://localhost:8081/api/events
Body (JSON):
Edit
{
  "title": "My Milestone",
  "category": "Personal",
  "description": "Graduated!",
  "date": "2020-06-01"
}
ğŸ”¹ Get All Events:
GET http://localhost:8081/api/events
(Use same Basic Auth)

ğŸ”¹ Update Event:
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/events/{id}
(Replace {id} with actual event ID)

ğŸ”¹ Delete Event:
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/events/{id}
___________________________________________________________________________________________________
ğŸ”’ Notes on Security:
Since using httpBasic() in SecurityConfig, every request must include Basic Auth credentials.
Later, we can also switch to JWT for token-based authentication if preferred.
Note: JWT is better for modern APIs (especially for Angular frontend). 









(Use same Basic Auth)
